'''Tommy Ryman''' (born March 17, 1983) is an American [[stand-up comedy|stand-up comedian]]<ref>http://www.southernminn.com/faribault_daily_news/news/article_4531ef5b-3d34-52bf-b447-b800c73b3fe2.html</ref> who was a semifinalist on the 2014 season of the TV Show [[Last Comic Standing]].<ref>{{cite news | last = | first = | title = Five Twin Cities comedians on revived ‘Last Comic Standing’ | url = https://www.twincities.com/2014/05/19/five-twin-cities-comedians-on-revived-last-comic-standing/ | work = [[St. Paul Pioneer Press]] | date = May 19, 2014 }}</ref> After getting his start in the [[Minnesota]] comedy scene, [[Paste (magazine)]] named him one of ''12 Great Stand-Up Comedians from the Midwest''.<ref>https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2016/03/12-great-stand-up-comedians-from-the-midwest.html</ref> In 2015, he won ''Best of Midwest'' at ''Gilda's Laugh Fest''.<ref>http://www.laughspin.com/tommy-ryman-named-best-of-midwest-at-gildas-laughfest-review/</ref> In 2018, he was invited to perform at the ''Great American Comedy Festival'' at [[Johnny Carson]] Theater <ref>http://hpr1.com/index.php/feature/best-bets/comedy-in-the-cellar-tommy-ryman/</ref>, first performing there in 2010<ref>http://thecomicscomic.com/2010/06/17/ed-asner-to-be-honored-at-third-annual-great-american-comedy-festival-in-nebraska/</ref>. He refrains from [[off-color humor]], instead relying on [[observational comedy]], sarcasm, and satire; in doing so, he gained recognition in 2018 on [[VidAngel]]'s Dry Bar Comedy Season 3 series entitled ''Activated''<ref>http://drybarcomedy.com</ref>.
==Personal== Tommy married his wife, Megan, in 2013 and the ceremony was officiated by comedian and actor [[Rob Little]]<ref>http://www.citypages.com/arts/comedian-rob-little-wants-to-marry-you-but-no-exorcisms-please-7812713</ref>. They reside in [[Redondo Beach, California]]<ref>http://tbrnews.com/entertainment/redondo-beach-comedian-tommy-ryman-releases-second-album/article_fbdfff1e-36a9-11e8-983f-9bdbf6784081.html</ref>. His mother is folk singer-songwriter [http://www.barbryman.com Barb Ryman]<ref>https://www.brownpapertickets.com/event/91506</ref>. His early comedic inspiration came from the late [[Mitch Hedberg]].<ref>http://www.citypages.com/arts/standup-tommy-rymans-breakthrough-year-7427158</ref>
